name: Google Analytics
description: This is the main class of an extension, is the entry point from which configurations, connection providers, operations and sources are going to be declared.

displayModel.summary: An Unique Google Analytics Profile ID to get Analytics Data

The desired output type for the Analytics data returned in the response
The aggregated statistics for user activity to your site, such as clicks or pageviews
The dimensions parameter breaks down metrics by common criteria; for example, by ga:browser or ga:city
Sorting the results of a query enables you to ask different questions about your data. For example, to address the question What are my top countries, and which browsers do they use most?

The filters query string parameter restricts the data returned from your request.For example, the following query requests ga:pageviews and ga:browser for view (profile) 12134, where the ga:browser dimension starts with the string Firefox:
Isolate and analyze subsets of your data, For example Select users who used Chrome browser in at least one of their sessions
